TEXT.TITLE: FCOJ MOVEMENT 3,915,370 GALLONS LAST WEEK
TEXT.BODY: Florida Citrus Processors Association said frozen concentrate orange juice movement into trade channels in the week ended March 7 totalled 3,915,370 gallons versus 3,956,126 gallons in the week ended February 28 and 4,284,693 gallons in the corresponding year-ago period. There were 3,814,891 gallons of foreign imports last week versus 133,505 gallons the week before. Domestic imports last week were 306,031. Retail movement was 1,652,916 versus 2,015,953 a year ago. Bulk movement was 1,934,494 against 1,954,103 a year earlier. Current season cumulative movement was 60,480,375 gallons versus 59,654,702 last year. Cumulative net pack for the season was 80,359,978 versus 74,071,755 a year ago. Inventory was 83,422,435 versus 81,963,040 a year ago. Reuter
